pgvector adds vector similarity search to PostgreSQL. Combined with LLM embeddings, it enables semantic search.

```sql
-- Enable extension
CREATE EXTENSION vector;

-- Add embedding column
ALTER TABLE knowledge_nodes ADD COLUMN embedding vector(1536);

-- Create HNSW index for fast similarity search
CREATE INDEX ON knowledge_nodes USING hnsw (embedding vector_cosine_ops);
```

```typescript
// Generate embedding
const embedding = await openai.embeddings.create({
  model: 'text-embedding-3-small',
  input: query,
});

// Similarity search with Drizzle
const results = await db.execute(sql`
  SELECT id, title, body,
    1 - (embedding <=> ${embedding.data[0].embedding}::vector) AS similarity
  FROM knowledge_nodes
  WHERE embedding IS NOT NULL
  ORDER BY embedding <=> ${embedding.data[0].embedding}::vector
  LIMIT 10
`);
```

Key decisions:
- text-embedding-3-small (1536d): good quality, cheaper
- text-embedding-3-large (3072d): better quality, 2x storage
- HNSW vs IVFFlat: HNSW has better recall, IVFFlat builds faster

Circuit breakers prevent cascading failures by failing fast when a downstream service is unhealthy.

```typescript
class CircuitBreaker {
  private failures = 0;
  private lastFailure = 0;
  private state: 'closed' | 'open' | 'half-open' = 'closed';

  constructor(
    private threshold: number = 5,
    private resetTimeout: number = 60_000,
  ) {}

  async call<T>(fn: () => Promise<T>): Promise<T> {
    if (this.state === 'open') {
      if (Date.now() - this.lastFailure > this.resetTimeout) {
        this.state = 'half-open';
      } else {
        throw new Error('Circuit breaker is open');
      }
    }

    try {
      const result = await fn();
      this.onSuccess();
      return result;
    } catch (err) {
      this.onFailure();
      throw err;
    }
  }

  private onSuccess() {
    this.failures = 0;
    this.state = 'closed';
  }

  private onFailure() {
    this.failures++;
    this.lastFailure = Date.now();
    if (this.failures >= this.threshold) this.state = 'open';
  }
}
```

Use one circuit breaker per downstream service. Log state transitions for observability.

```typescript
import { and, or, eq, like, gt, SQL } from 'drizzle-orm';

function buildFilters(params: {
  type?: string;
  trust?: string;
  minScore?: number;
  search?: string;
}) {
  const conditions: SQL[] = [];

  if (params.type) conditions.push(eq(nodes.type, params.type));
  if (params.trust) conditions.push(eq(nodes.trustLevel, params.trust));
  if (params.minScore) conditions.push(gt(nodes.score, params.minScore));
  if (params.search) {
    conditions.push(
      or(
        like(nodes.title, `%${params.search}%`),
        like(nodes.body, `%${params.search}%`)
      )!
    );
  }

  return conditions.length > 0 ? and(...conditions) : undefined;
}

const results = await db.select()
  .from(nodes)
  .where(buildFilters({ type: 'answer', minScore: 10 }))
  .limit(20);
```

This pattern avoids string concatenation SQL injection and keeps queries type-safe.

